data.name: Common_Key_Help
data.value: The key is used to identify this item in scripts and must be unique with respect to it's parent. One a key has been assigned, it can not be changed.

data.name: Common_Key_Validation
data.value: The key must 1) begin with a lower case letter, 2) contain only lower case letters and numbers, and 3) must be between 3 and 50 characters.

data.name: Component_Description
data.value: A component is part that can be used to assemble a PCB or device

data.name: ComponentPackage_Description
data.value: A component package is the physical package that makes up a component.

data.name: ComponentPackage_CenterY_Help
data.value: Center Y from the reference hole in the tape

data.name: PartPack_Description
data.value: Part Packs are strip feeders with identified parts on board.

data.name: StripFeeder_Description
data.value: A strip feeder is a container for components where a tape is installed, each part is picked in a new location based on how many parts are in the strip

data.name: PackAndPlace_Description
data.value: A Pick and Place job has the parameters for a job that should be run on a pick and place machine

data.name: StripFeederRow_Description
data.value: A row within a strip feeder

data.name: Machine_Description
data.value: Machine are XY, GCode based such as a Pick and Place Machine, a Laser Cutter or CNC Machine

data.name: Pcb_Description
data.value: Printed circuit boards are electronic components

data.name: Pcb_Revision_Description
data.value: A circuit board revision is a version of a board with a specific layout and component set.

data.name: Pcb_Variant_Description
data.value: A variant is a spec for building a board with a specific set of components on it. A board may have more components than it needs.

data.name: ComponentOrder_Description
data.value: An order of parts from a supplier

data.name: ComponentOrderLineItem_Received_Help
data.value: Has this item been put into inventory.

data.name: ComponentAttribute_Description
data.value: A component attribute is a component specific value that describes the part such as resistance, capacitance and so on.

data.name: ComponentPackage_Verified_Help
data.value: Has this package been verifed correct

data.name: NozzleTip_Description
data.value: A nozzle tip is an attachment that goes on a pick and place head that will place parts, there are difference sizes to allow picking up differnet size components

data.name: MachineStagingPlate_Description
data.value: A staging plate is the surface of the machine with holes at fixed locations that allow feeders, boards and equipment to be attached.

data.name: MachineStagingPlate_FirstHole_Help
data.value: Distance from Origin (Bottom Left) to First Hole. This is used to generate the grid. Reference Hole Column, Row and Location are used to accurately place the staging plate in the workspace

data.name: MachineStagingPlate_Origin_Help
data.value: Location of the bottom left of the staging plate with respect to the frame origin. This is used to render the machine graphics. Accurate information will be captured with Reference Hole Column, Row and Location.

data.name: ToolNozzleTip_Description
data.value: A Nozzle Tip is placed at the end of a nozzle and is used to pickup parts. Different size nozzle tips are used to pick up different parts

data.name: Common_Origin_Help
data.value: The bottom left XY coordinate of the object

data.name: StripFeeder_RowOneRefHoleOffset
data.value: Row One - Tap Hole Offset from Origin

data.name: MachineStagingPlate_HolesStaggered_Help
data.value: This is true if the the holes are diagonally aligned, this is false if the holes are in solid lines.

data.name: StripFeeder_RowOneRefHoleOffset_Help
data.value: The offset from the origin or bottom left of the feeder to the reference hole for the first row, assuming that the the tape holes are in the top of the feeder.

data.name: StripFeeder_AngleOffset_Help
data.value: The angle offset for this strip feeder to correct for any installation errors. This is usually calibrated by the machine and not manually entered.

data.name: Machine_FeederRail_Description
data.value: A feeder rail is attached to a machine, automated feeders are attached to the feeder rail, the feeder rail has slots where the feeders are positioned.

data.name: Machine_FeederRail_FirstFeederOrigin_Help
data.value: The XY location of the first feeder with respect to the center of the feeder rail and center of the feeder body. This value can be obtained by finding the center of the rail in the Y Axis and center of the body of the first feeder in the X Axis (assuming the feeders are aligned with the Y Axis of the machine.

data.name: GCode_ParseStatusRegularExpressionHelp
data.value: This regular expression should read the values from the status message and return the following groups (xpos) = current X position; (ypos) = current Y position; (zpos) current Z position; (lrot) rotate of the left pick head; (rrot) = rotate of the right pick head (if applicable)

data.name: Machine_GCode_Description
data.value: Defines GCode Commands and how those results should be parsed.

data.name: Machine_WorkAreaOrigin_Help
data.value: Offset from the bottom left of the frame to the bottom left of the work area.

data.name: GCode_Description
data.value: A GCode mapping file defines the GCodes that are used to sent to a machine.

data.name: MachineStagingPlate_ReferenceHoleCol_Help
data.value: Column where the hole to identify the staging plate location is located.

data.name: MachineStagingPlate_ReferenceHoleRow_Help
data.value: Row in which the reference hole is located to identify staging plate location

data.name: MachineStagingPlate_ReferenceHoleLocation_Help
data.value: XY Coodinate of the center of the refrence hole to identify staging plate location. This is generally set via machine vision and not through the web interface. Two points are used to compensate for installation angle errors.

data.name: StripFeeder_ReferenceHoleOffset_Help
data.value: Provide the XY offset from the bottom left origin of the strip feeder to the reference hole location. This is assuming that the feeder is horizontal and is used to determine where the feeder origin is located.

data.name: StripFeeder_ReferenceHole_Row_Help
data.value: The row of the hole in the staging plate where the strip feeder reference hole is mounted.

data.name: StripFeeder_ReferenceHole_Col_Help
data.value: The column of the staging plate where the reference hole of the strip feeder is mounted.

data.name: PickAndPlaceJob_Description
data.value: A pick and place job is a configuration of a circuit board revision that is to be built. This include which parts should be placed.

data.name: Machine_FeederRail_StartSlotIndex_Help
data.value: Feeder rail indexes are at the machine level. If you have more than one feeder rail, you can configure that start index here.

data.name: Feeder_AdvanceGCode_Help
data.value: GCode used to advance the feeder. Will replace the following parameters {slot} {feederid} within the GCode.

data.name: MachineToolHead_Description
data.value: The Tool Head is the part of the machine that will do the work such as a place head or router.

data.name: MachineToolHead_PickHeight_Help
data.value: Pick Height for this tool head that does not include the height of the nozzle.

data.name: MachineToolHead_PlaceHight_Help
data.value: Place Height for this tool head that does not include the height of the nozzle.

data.name: MachineCamera_Description
data.value: Camera that is attached to the machine

data.name: MachineCamera_PixelsPerMM_Help
data.value: Place a ruler on to the work surface turn on the 200 pixel square in the camera view. Note the number of millimeters in 200 pixels, dive the number of millimeters by 200 and enter that number.

data.name: Feeder_PickOffsetFromSlotOrigin_Help
data.value: Offset from the known point or fiducial of the feeder.

data.name: Feeder_FiducialOffsetFromSlotOriign_Help
data.value: The offset from the origin on the feeder rail to the location of the fiducial on the feeder.

data.name: AutoFeederTemplate_Description
data.value: Default parameters that can be used to create auto feeders. The origin of the Auto Feeder will be calculated from the slot location and is the horizontal center of the feeder on the top of the rail.

data.name: StripFeederTemplate_Description
data.value: Default Parameters used to create Strip Feeders. Dimensions as entered expect that the feeder is oriented horizontally. A strip feeder is a container for components where a tape is installed, each part is picked in a new location based on how many parts are in the strip.

data.name: Machine_WorkspaceFrameOffset_Help
data.value: Distance in MM from the bottom, front left of the machines frame to the 0,0 coordinate of the workspace.

data.name: StripFeederRow_LastTapeHoleOffset_Help
data.value: Offset from tape hole prior to first part to tape hole prior to last part, used to correct for any angle offsets in feeder installation.

data.name: StripFeederRow_FirstTapeHoleOffset_Help
data.value: Offset from feeder origina point to first tape hole prior to first part. This offset assumes that the feeder is install horizintally and will be automatically set and corrected if the feeder is installed vertically

data.name: StripFeeder_FeederSize_Help
data.value: The size of the feeder in MM, assume that the width will be horizontal so the tape runs on the X access. The length with be the X axis. The width will be the Y axis and Z will be total dimension in the Z access of the physical feeder. The location at which parts are picked is specified in the Pick Height field.

data.name: StripFeeder_PickHeight_Help
data.value: The Z location or height at which the nozzle tip should be set to pickup a part from the tape. This will be the same for each part.

data.name: StripFeeder_RowWidth_Help
data.value: The actual width of each row to include spacing between rows. This is used to calculate the tape reference hole locatoin wiht respect to row index and first role offset.

data.name: Feeder_FeederId_Help
data.value: This is a user generated ID value that can be used to create something like a human readable label, a QR Code or NFC tag to be able to identify the feeder.

data.name: Feeder_FeederWidth_Help
data.value: Width of the feeder, this is only used for rendering the feeder and shold be the widest part of the feeder.

data.name: Feeder_FeederHeight_Help
data.value: The height or how tall the feeder is, this is only used for rendering the feeder and should be the largest height dimension.

data.name: Feeder_FeederLength_Help
data.value: The length of the feeder, this is only used for rending the feeder and should be longest dimenions of the feeder.

data.name: Feeder_OriginOffset_Help
data.value: Offset from the center of the slot where the feeder is installed to the origin or bottom left of the of feender. This is primarily used to render the feeder.

data.name: MachineStagingPlate_FirstRowOddOnly_Help
data.value: If the holes on the staging plate are stagger is the first row odd columns only

data.name: MachineStagingPlate_LastUsableColumn_Help
data.value: What is the last column on the staging plate where the machine can access.

data.name: MachineStagingPlate_FirstUsableColumn_Help
data.value: What is the last column on the staging plate where the machine can access.

data.name: PickAndPlaceJobRun_Description
data.value: A Pick and Place Job Run is an instance of a Pick and Place Job that tracks the creation of the creation of a circuit board

data.name: AutoFeeder_Size_Help
data.value: The size of the AutoFeeder, this is primarily used for rendering a block that represents the feeder. The X axis will represent the length and is likely the longer distance of the feeder. Width of the feeder is the usualy the smallest value and height is from the bottom to the top of the feeder.

data.name: Machine_WorkAreaSize_Help
data.value: The Work Area Size is the XY grid that is accessible via GCode. It's the location at 0,0 to the upper bounds that your machine supports. This does not include the frame sizes that extends beyond the work area.

data.name: Machine_FrameSize_Help
data.value: The total physical size of the frame for your machine. This is primarily used for rending and should be a rectangle.

data.name: AutoFeeder_Description
data.value: An auto feeder is one that typically uses a tap real to dispense parts. The feeder pick point remains the same but the tape is advanced with each part.
